### 6.1 Temporal Fragmentation
Self becomes inconsistent across time.
- dissociation  
- memory incoherence  
- unstable narrative  

### 6.2 Narrative Collapse
Self loses coherent story.
- meaninglessness  
- depersonalization  
- emotional flattening  

### 6.3 Recursive Drift
Self‑reference becomes unstable.
- inconsistent self‑evaluation  
- identity inversion  
- runaway recursion  

### 6.4 Boundary Rupture
Self loses containment.
- depersonalization  
- identity leakage  
- instability  

Failure modes mirror field and contradiction breakdown.

